A vintage-style technical blueprint illustration on aged cream paper with subtle coffee stains, showing an exploded view of nested Russian matryoshka dolls, but instead of painted faces, each doll shell contains intricate mechanical gears and clockwork components visible through cutaway sections. The innermost doll glows with warm amber light, representing the core data. Delicate hand-drawn arrows and dotted lines connect the layers, suggesting parameter flow between nested components. The color palette features deep indigo ink, brass metallics, and touches of oxidized copper green. Architectural drafting style with precise cross-hatching and dimensional perspective, reminiscent of Leonardo da Vinci's technical sketches combined with Victorian-era engineering diagrams.
